Description:
TestTrivium16 is a TinyOS application which shows how the trivium interface can be used
for 16-bit microcontroller.
The programm creates two internal states which represents the states of a transmitter and
a receiver. A message is encrypted with the transmitter state and then decrypted with the
receiver state.

TestTrivum16AppC.nc :	The configuration file.

TestTrivium16C.nc :		The module file.


Installation:

If the tivium interface is installed in the TinyOS tree then this program can be compiled with
the command:

make [mote_name]

where [mote_name] is the name of the mote use, for example telosb.
Known bugs/limitations:

None.
